# Rural Digital Payments & Community Credit Score Platform

> **EPICS Project (Engineering Projects in Community Service)**
> A mobile-first solution bridging the financial gap in rural communities through accessible digital payments and alternative credit scoring.

![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg)
![Platform](https://img.shields.io/badge/platform-React%20Native%20%7C%20Android%20%7C%20iOS-orange)
![Language](https://img.shields.io/badge/language-TypeScript-blue)

## ğŸ“– Overview

This project is developed as part of the **EPICS (Engineering Projects in Community Service)** curriculum. It aims to solve two critical issues in rural finance:
1.  **Accessibility:** Providing a simple, low-bandwidth digital payment interface for users with limited tech literacy.
2.  **Creditworthiness:** Establishing a "Community Credit Score" system that leverages transaction history and community trust factors to enable micro-lending for individuals without formal banking history.

## âœ¨ Key Features

* ** Simplified Digital Wallet**: Easy-to-use interface for sending and receiving money, optimized for rural connectivity.
* ** ğŸ“Š Community Credit Score**: A proprietary algorithm that calculates a dynamic credit score based on repayment habits and community endorsements.
* ** ğŸ“± Offline/Low-Data Mode**: Core features designed to function efficiently in areas with unstable internet connections.
* ** ğŸ” Secure Transactions**: End-to-end encryption for all financial data.
* ** ğŸ‘¥ Community Groups**: Support for Self-Help Groups (SHGs) to manage pooled funds and internal lending.

## ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

* **Frontend**: React Native (Expo)
* **Language**: TypeScript
* **State Management**: React Context API / Redux (Planned)
* **Navigation**: React Navigation
* **Styling**: StyleSheet / NativeBase

## ğŸš€ Getting Started

Follow these instructions to set up the project locally on your machine.

### Prerequisites

* [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (v14 or newer)
* [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/) or [yarn](https://yarnpkg.com/)
* [Expo Go](https://expo.dev/client) app installed on your physical device (Android/iOS).

### Installation

1.  **Clone the repository:**
    ```bash
    git clone [https://github.com/AdityaaaSharmaaa/EPICS-Project.git](https://github.com/AdityaaaSharmaaa/EPICS-Project.git)
    cd EPICS-Project
    ```

2.  **Install dependencies:**
    ```bash
    npm install
    # or
    yarn install
    ```

3.  **Start the development server:**
    ```bash
    npx expo start
    ```

4.  **Run on Device:**
    * Scan the QR code displayed in the terminal using the **Expo Go** app on your phone.
    * Ensure your phone and computer are on the same Wi-Fi network.

